                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=akeller",
                        "name": "akeller",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Keller",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I had this problem as well and used the $schema parameter to work around it.\r\n\r\n{code:title=Zend_Db_Select with database.schema.table|borderStyle=solid}\r\n$select = $db->select()\r\n             ->from(array('t' => 'table'), '*', 'database.schema')\r\n             ->joinLeft(array('t2' => 'jointable'), 't.id = t2.id', '*', 'database.schema');\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis is working for me on version 1.11.11 of the Zend Framework.  But I agree it would be great for Zend_Db_Select to accept the database.schema.table syntax in the first parameter.",
